#Advantages of spring
1. Modular and lightweights
2. Flexible configuration
3. Dependency injection (DI)
4. Aspect oriented programming (AOP)
5. Simplified Databases access
6. Testing support
7. Security
8. Integration capability
9. Scalability
10. Open source

- Spring container(heart of spring)
Types of spring containers = Bean factory(old) and Application context(new)
Application context is interface.

POJO(Plain Old Java Object) class - Class with properties and getter and setter

Configuration file provided through - xml file, java file, annotations file

JdbcTemplate classs = it is central class in Spring-JDBC module
it is used to perform database operations (CRUD Operations)
Methods JdbcTemplates contains all query methods

Dependency injection done by two ways : 1. constructor through  2. Autowired

